Education.

Bachelor in Software Enginneering

UNICESUMAR / 2019 - Incomplete

I studied for three years, gaining knowledge that has been valuable in my work. Although I was unable to complete the course, I hope to finish it in the future.

Unity Basic Course

Alura / 2020

The Alura Unity Basic Course provided me with an introduction to Unity development. The course covers creating small games, such as Flappy Bird and a zombie survival game, while also teaching how to use the Unity engine and code basic features in C#.

Certification in C#

Alura / 2020

Earning a certification in C# was an incredible experience, as it allowed me to master the C# language, covering everything from basic to advanced topics. The program included practical activities and provided in-depth coverage of each subject we studied.

Experience.

Unity VR Developer

MedRoom / 2022 - Current

At MedRoom, as a Unity VR Developer, I began my role by developing a complex Oropharynx exam using physics objects and blendshapes. This exam required the simulation of inspecting a patient's mouth with a tongue depressor, a flashlight, and animation triggers.



Following the completion of the Oropharynx exam, I focused on resolving project bugs. I consider this to be one of the most valuable aspects of the job, as it provides deep insight into the entire project. This process allowed me to familiarize myself with every component, which ultimately helped me better support my team.



Next, I was tasked with redesigning the project's entire UI. Collaborating closely with the design team, I led the overhaul, which involved creating the foundational code and automations for the new interface. Key improvements included automating UI generation for new exams, revamping the exam access interface, updating patient information displays, implementing a new tooltips system, and creating a new UI for questions and answers.



I then worked on developing a series of abdominal exams alongside another developer. We meticulously crafted the entire process for routine abdominal examinations, mirroring a doctor's approach with a patient. This included inspection, palpation, percussion, and more, totaling 11 exams, many of which featured animations, trigger points, and blendshapes.



My most recent and final task involved developing two groups of complex exams: Reflexes and Motor. These exams are critical for confirming diagnoses in specific cases, requiring precise doctor-patient interactions, animation synchronization, and interface interactions. Some exams demanded detailed point-by-point interaction with the patient, where the doctor’s hand needed to be accurately positioned on the patient’s body while the patient moved. I developed all 11 exams in this package, and toward the end of the project, I collaborated with colleagues to polish the final product and resolve any remaining issues.

Internal Unity Game Developer at LIGA

LIGA Facens - 2021 / 2022

As an intern at LIGA, I handled a variety of tasks related to Unity development. LIGA focuses on developing mobile games with Unity. My first project at LIGA was a match-3 game, created using a purchased template from the Unity Store. I was responsible for reskinning the game, configuring and adjusting the level difficulties, and fixing various bugs in the project. Additionally, I was tasked with building and deploying the game to the Google Play Store and Apple App Store. This involved managing all store configurations and resolving issues that arose during the publishing process.



My second and final project was a Bingo game, which is essentially a match game where random numbers are drawn, and each player marks them on their board. It’s a multiplayer game with real-time matchmaking. In this project, I collaborated with a more senior developer, but I also contributed significantly to the development. We used Photon to manage the multiplayer networking, which greatly facilitated the process. This game was also successfully published in the stores.
